37922>>>
37922>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
37922>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
37922>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
37922>>>        Case Begin
37922>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
37924>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
37924>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
37924>>>                Case Break
37925>>>                
37925>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
37928>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
37928>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
37928>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
37928>>>                Case Break
37929>>>                
37929>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
37932>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
37932>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
37932>>>                Case Break
37933>>>                
37933>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
37933>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
37933>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
37933>>>                  
37933>>>        Case End
37933>>>
37933>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
37933>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
37933>>>        Send SetActionButtons
37934>>>
37934>>>    End_Procedure
37935>>>
37935>>>End_Object
