38232>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
38232>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
38232>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
38235>>>
38235>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
38235>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
38235>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
38235>>>        Case Begin
38235>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
38237>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
38237>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
38237>>>                Case Break
38238>>>                
38238>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
38241>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
38241>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
38241>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
38241>>>                Case Break
38242>>>                
38242>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
38245>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
38245>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
38245>>>                Case Break
38246>>>                
38246>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
38246>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
38246>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
38246>>>                  
38246>>>        Case End
38246>>>
38246>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
38246>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
38246>>>        Send SetActionButtons
38247>>>
38247>>>    End_Procedure
38248>>>
38248>>>End_Object
